        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Mary Engel, aka Mary Engelberg, was the author of a labor-themed movie script/screenplay.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Consists of "The Winner," a movie script/screenplay (114 pp.) It begins in 1936 in a union hall, in Monessen, PA (the local union represents workers at the "Spartacus Tin Plate Company"). It concludes years later with union corruption and murder, with the word "winner" in the title apparently referring to a corrupt union official who rose out of the rank and file.</p>
        </scopecontent>
